The city prospered as Izotus under the Hellenist rule, until [[马加比家族|马加比革命]]. During the rebellion [[Judas_Maccabeus|Judas Maccabeus]] arrived at its gates, but didn't conquer it. He had left it behind for his brother [[Jonathan|Jonathan]], who conquered it in 147 BCE and destroyed the [[Temple|Temple]] of [[Dagon|Dagon]]. According to Josephus (''Antiquities of the Jews'' 13:15, volume 4), Alexander Jannæus possessed it. Pompey restored its independence in that he reconstructed its walls, though it belonged to the dominion of Herod and Salome (''Antiquities...'' 17:18, volume 9), and Vespasian had to take it by force. -->

